Flight mode is a function that '''inactivates''' [[radio transmitters]] and receivers so that some functions (e.g. music and [[java games|games]] can be used in places such as planes and hospitals.

In recent this most often applies to a growing trend of mobile phones, but can obviously apply to any electronic device that primarily transmits radio signals as its main usage.
Despite the name, the function is not legally allowed to use on public flight as there is no clear indication whether or not a phone is actually transmitting data, therefore users simply treat it as a ''power-saving'' feature.

The [[Sony Ericsson W800]] mobile phone was first to introduce this feature since first launching its [[Walkman]]-brand phone.